al-align: baseline; color: rgb(34, 61, 117); text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out 0s;&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Chris Moran Senior solutions delivery manager at Provident Financial&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&hellip;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;&ldquo;A key takeaway for me from the Digital Job Fair was that there is a noticeable shift in the focus for technology graduates. &nbsp;I struggle to recruit experienced software professionals with a strong focus on User Experience and the creative element. &nbsp;Typically software development has been a &ldquo;hard core&rdquo; discipline dominated by men. &nbsp;The people I spoke to at the fair demonstrated much more desire for careers in the creative / UX space &ndash; technologies such as Javascript, CSS and HTML were much more prevalent than traditional Java / .Net skills. &nbsp;Also, the majority of people I spoke to in this space were young women which I feel is a positive move for the industry as a whole.&rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;strong glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;On the rise of tech in The North, Chris has this to say&hellip;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '', 1, '', '', '', 'amsource-visits-leeds-digital-job-fair', 'yes', 'yes', 1586822400),
(6, 'Recruiting in the connected world', 0, '', '', '87b596e9b993af2c7e68599166741d35.png', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;The modern day recruiter needs a set of skills, tools and an approach that has changed and developed over the last 10 years. &nbsp;You need to be open with an all-inclusive approach &ndash; not evasive, secretive and with an attitude like something from Wolf of Wall Street.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Here I give some thoughts in what I think are the key attributes we should be adopting as recruiters in a modern, connected and open world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;strong glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Delivery Focussed&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;As recruiters we&rsquo;re here to provide a service, and the ability to deliver on that service is crucial. &nbsp;Setting expectations, meeting deadlines and working with a high level of skill and expertise is a must. &nbsp;However, if you can&rsquo;t deliver you need to explain why and provide alternative and realistic solutions. &nbsp;You won&rsquo;t lose credibility for explaining why you can&rsquo;t deliver on something if you provide details as to why!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;strong glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Expert market knowledge&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;You need to become an expert in your chosen market, as this allows you to add significant value to your clients. &nbsp;We&rsquo;re not talking about sitting down and writing code (although that would be good.) but we are saying you need to know your Java from your Javascript as a minimum! &nbsp;You need to understand key skills and how they fit into your market and know who the key hiring companies and key influencers are.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;strong glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Be a Partner Adding Value&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;This goes without saying, but what we&rsquo;re talking about is adding value beyond putting bums on seats and managing a process. &nbsp;Recruiters should partner with organisations, being a confidant providing sound market intelligence and contributing to the wider community. &nbsp;This can be through attending events, organising events and being integrated into a clients recruitment process through an RPO approach or basics such managed interviews. &nbsp;Adding value builds your credibility in your market.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;strong glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Quality over Quantity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;You&rsquo;re paid to provide a service to improve a company&rsquo;s hiring processes, not to add to it. &nbsp;Work on a quality basis, not quantity. &nbsp;Only send relevant CV&rsquo;s, and pick up the phone to explain why you haven&rsquo;t. &nbsp;Don&rsquo;t send CV&rsquo;s to show you&rsquo;re working in the background, doing so means the client are wasting energy sifting unsuitable candidates, and you&rsquo;re wasting the candidates time if they&rsquo;re clearly unsuitable against the role profile. &nbsp;Oh, and don&rsquo;t send a CV without clearly telling the candidate where they&rsquo;re being sent &ndash; you&rsquo;re making everyone&#039;s lives a nightmare in the process. &nbsp;Just manage the process more effectively if you need to protect the clients name.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;strong glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Social&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;The whole world is going social, so Recruiters need to follow suit. &nbsp;Linkedin is a given, but modern recruiters are using tools such as Twitter, Facebook etc as well as investing in blogs. &nbsp;This is about building your personal brand, encouraging people in your network to be attracted to you rather than you having to do all the chasing. &nbsp;Recruitment God&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a glober=&quot;&quot; href=&quot;http://gregsavage.com.au/2015/05/05/recruitment-is-marketing-are-you-ready-for-that/&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Greg Savage talks about recruiters becoming marketeers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&ndash; take notice!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;strong glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Influential&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;It is vital the modern recruiter has the ability to influence. &nbsp;Gone are the days of boiler-room sales tactics of the 80&rsquo;s and 90&rsquo;s. &nbsp;We need to be in tune with our clients and candidates and the markets we operate, providing sound information to attract candidates to join our clients, and to encourage clients to use our services. &nbsp;It&rsquo;s important we influence in a positive manner, not by bad mouthing others.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;strong glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Personal Brand&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;You need to build a personal brand. &nbsp;Your actions and approach coupled with your attitude and ability to tell people about it across multiple channels is your personal brand. &nbsp;What do you want people to think of you and how will that encourage them engage with you now, and for the long-term? &nbsp;We&rsquo;re in the millennial age where information is created and stored for eternity &ndash; If your name is typed into Google what will it say about you&hellip;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;What attributes do you think are most important for the modern day recruiter?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Tweet us&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a glober=&quot;&quot; href=&quot;https://twitter.com/AmsourceTech&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;@AmsourceTech&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '', 8, '', '', '', 'recruiting-in-the-connected-world', 'yes', 'no', 1430784000);
INSERT INTO `club_blog` (`id`, `title`, `consultant_id`, `subtitle`, `subtitle2`, `image`, `content`, `content_before`, `sector`, `meta_title`, `meta_keywords`, `meta_desc`, `slug`, `posted`, `deleted`, `time`) VALUES
(7, 'Tech//Connect 1.4, DevOps: Culture &amp; Containers', 0, '', '', '0426435e9c12353c18c9ad79f0b73cc4.png', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;a glober=&quot;&quot; href=&quot;https://www.amsourcetechnology.com/news/infographic-top-skills-to-succeed-in-devops-62163843399&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;DevOps&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is one of the biggest buzzwords in the software / digital community at the moment, working in conjunction with Continuous Delivery and Agile processes. &nbsp;The collision of development and operations aims to enhance communication and collaboration between software developers and IT professionals. &nbsp;The rapid growth of this market, and the benefits that come with it have undoubtedly caused a considerable increase in the demand of skilled DevOps professionals.&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;On Thursday 17th November we held the fourth event in our series of&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Tech//Connect events&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;, DevOps: Culture &amp; Containers. &nbsp;The event brought together software professionals from across our region where they were invited to listen to talks surrounding two key areas in DevOps, take part in a Q&amp;A where they were able to ask any burning questions about DevOps and network with other like-minded professionals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;It was a great opportunity for those who haven&rsquo;t yet implemented DevOps into their working environment, to see the benefits of doing so, and also gave those who are already using DevOps some further insight into overcoming challenges they may encounter.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;We were joined by 2 guest speakers &ndash;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a glober=&quot;&quot; href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/in/chris-urwin-9370422?authType=NAME_SEARCH&amp;authToken=JauD&amp;locale=en_US&amp;trk=tyah&amp;trkInfo=clickedVertical%3Amynetwork%2CclickedEntityId%3A6059707%2CauthType%3ANAME_SEARCH%2Cidx%3A1-1-1%2CtarId%3A1479912167098%2Ctas%3Achris%20urwin&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Chris Urwin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a glober=&quot;&quot; href=&quot;http://rancher.com/&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Rancher Labs&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a glober=&quot;&quot; href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/in/clement-pickering-83a549b?authType=NAME_SEARCH&amp;authToken=cuNL&amp;locale=en_US&amp;trk=tyah&amp;trkInfo=clickedVertical%3Amynetwork%2CclickedEntityId%3A34189678%2CauthType%3ANAME_SEARCH%2Cidx%3A1-1-1%2CtarId%3A1479912342148%2Ctas%3AClement%20Pickering&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Clem Pickering&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a glober=&quot;&quot; href=&quot;https://www.infinityworks.com/&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Infinity Works Consulting&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;. &nbsp;Clem delivered a talk all about DevOps culture, and the &lsquo;elephant&rsquo; in the room when it comes to DevOps and common preconceptions. &nbsp;Chris presented an interesting talk all about containerisation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Chris discussed the adoption of a container strategy, where to start, the gotchas to avoid and the benefits it can bring. &nbsp;Chris used real life-examples from his experience at Rancher working with large and small, public and private sector organisations to develop and implement container strategies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Chris received a series of interesting questions after the presentation that included &ldquo;What is the difference between virtualisation and containers?&rdquo; And &ldquo;If containers share an operating system how secure are they?&rdquo; &nbsp;Chris provided the room with unbiased answers showing the pros and cons of adopting a container strategy. &nbsp;Notably Chris did inform the room that as container technology stands, having a full containerised environment is probably not advisable for various reasons including security and struggles with databases, but if implemented to the correct parts of the environment it can have massive benefits including the ability to run containers on any computer, on any infrastructure and in any cloud.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Clem&rsquo;s talk was focussed on the fact that bringing DevOps into an organisation is not just implementing a set of tools it is about implementing a specific culture and thought process. &nbsp;After Clem&rsquo;s presentation he received questions from those with already established &ldquo;DevOps&rdquo; teams and those who are at the beginning of the journey. &nbsp;Some of the main topics discussed in the Q&amp;A included on &ldquo;How to get buy-in from Executive team / board?&rdquo; &nbsp;and &ldquo;Ability of existing team to upskill &amp; how to do this?&rdquo; &nbsp;As with most of these style of questions Clem revealed that the process of implementing DevOps is different for every organisation and there is no magic formula, however if done correctly it can provide many benefits including a shorter development life cycle and greater stability and reliability.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;strong glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;Check out video footage from the event here&hellip;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;iframe allowfullscreen=&quot;&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; glober=&quot;&quot; height=&quot;315&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/MbS5fL01gNE&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 400; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;br glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;span glober=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 65, 122); font-family: &quot; w01=&quot;&quot;&gt;The evening was a great success, the feedback we have received so far has been really positive and it would seem that attendees of the event were able to take home some helpful knowledge that will be valuable to them on their DevOps journey.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;div class=&quot;SandboxRoot env-bp-350&quot; data-twitter-event-id=&quot;0&quot; segoe=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;display: block; max-height: 10000px; direction: ltr; text-align: left; background: 0px 0px; font: 16px / 1.4 Helvetica, Roboto, &quot; ui=&quot;&quot;&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;EmbeddedTweet EmbeddedTweet-